Program: Outlook
Title: 19/06/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00t7x38
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 20 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, as the Greek Government struggles to deal with the austerity measures imposed on the country, the director of a psychiatric hospital tells us how his four hundred patients are in danger of starvation. Also, Matthew Bannister hears from an American reporter who has witnessed hundreds of executions in Texas - Michael Graczyk tells Matthew why he sees this as part of his professional duty. And, as part of our Edible City series, Malaysian-born Dennis Lee talks about his journey from the markets of the island of Penang to the Royal College of Music in London. Show less